# 4-bit Adder Design & Simulation (Verilog)

## 📌 Project Overview

This project implements a **4-bit combinational adder** using Verilog HDL and verifies its functionality through simulation in ModelSim.

It serves as a fundamental "Hello World" project for digital IC design, covering the complete workflow from RTL design to simulation and waveform analysis.

---

## 🧠 Design Description

The adder takes two 4-bit inputs (`a`, `b`) and produces a 5-bit output (`sum`) to account for carry-out.

* Type: Combinational Logic
* Implementation: Continuous assignment (`assign`)
* Overflow handled via output width extension

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
01_adder/
├── adder.v          # RTL design of 4-bit adder
├── adder_tb.v       # Testbench for simulation
├── waveform.png     # Simulation waveform result
└── README.md        # Project documentation
```

---

## 🔧 Tools Used

* Verilog HDL
* ModelSim (simulation)
* Git & GitHub (version control)

---

## ▶️ How to Run Simulation

### Step 1: Compile

```tcl
vlog adder.v
vlog adder_tb.v
```

### Step 2: Simulate (disable optimization for waveform visibility)

```tcl
vsim -novopt adder_tb
```

### Step 3: Add waveform and run

```tcl
add wave -r /*
run 50ns
```

---

## 📊 Simulation Result

The waveform verifies correct addition behavior:

| a  | b | sum |
| -- | - | --- |
| 0  | 0 | 0   |
| 3  | 5 | 8   |
| 7  | 8 | 15  |
| 15 | 1 | 16  |

*(See waveform.png for detailed signal transitions)*

